\title{Negation rule}

\p{Using #{\bot} elimination, we can define \em{negation}:

##{\neg A \equiv_{\mathtt{def}} A \implies \bot}

and using this definition, we can define for negation its introduction rule:

##{\frac{\begin{array}{cc}
          [A] & [A] \\
          \vdots & \vdots \\
          B & \neg B
        \end{array}}
       {\neg A}(\mathtt{\neg{I}})}

and elimination:

##{\frac{\begin{array}{lr}
          A & \neg A \\
        \end{array}}
       {B}(\mathtt{\neg{E}})}}
